message: /* Historical context */ Deleted due to inaccuracies
/* Summary */Removed inaccuracies eluding to other authors which are not  "widely accepted" as the former version of this article claimed.
/* Structure */Fixed inaccuracies concerning the authorship of the Book.
Fixed inaccurate statements as to the authorship of the Book
Undid revision 685073360 by [[Special:Contributions/Darth Viller|Darth Viller]] ([[User talk:Darth Viller|talk]])
Removed speculation asserted as undisputed fact.
/* Historical context */ removed section containing speculation as undisputed historical fact.
undid revision claiming religious source.  The Book of Isaiah is itself a religious book.  References to Isaiah in the Bible (which is also historical) were historical references.

The prior edit deleted the new section "Nonsecular View of Authorship of the Book of Isaiah" is not copyrighted and verifiable by the scriptural sources quoted. The claim of "ample evidence" & "...no one believes" are disputed.
/* Authorship */ The non-secular view of the authorship of the Book of Isaiah.
